cs.SY, cs.AI, cs.DC, cs.SE, cs.CE 

The paper proposes a generic and scalable approach for quantitatively describing and pricing the flexibility of distributed energy resources, which involves control and market decisions. This suggests that the paper could belong to the Systems and Control (cs.SY), Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI), Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing (cs.DC), Software Engineering (cs.SE), or Computational Engineering, Finance, and Science (cs.CE) sub-categories.
